From: CrazyBoyFeng <crazyboyfeng@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] qualcommax: ipq50xx: pz-l8: add caldata entries with MAC patch

PR #21495 adds cmcc,pz-l8 to the ath11k caldata hotplug script but in a
"bare" form (caldata_extract only, no MAC patch). This causes ath11k to
use a random MAC on every boot for both 2.4GHz and 5GHz.

This patch inserts cmcc,pz-l8 case blocks with the full MAC patch:
  - 2.4GHz (IPQ5018): offset 0x1000, MAC = label_mac + 2
  - 5GHz (QCN6122):   offset 0x26800, MAC = label_mac + 3

label_mac is read from offset 0 of the ART partition (the device's base
MAC). The +2/+3 offsets follow the convention used by other ipq50xx
devices (e.g. yuncore,ax830 uses +2 for 2.4GHz, linksys,mx6200 uses +2
for 2.4GHz and +3 for 5GHz).

This patch is applied AFTER PR #21495 (which is applied with --exclude
for this caldata file), so it runs against a clean OpenWrt main caldata
file. The insert mode (vs replace mode) decouples this patch from PR
#21495's caldata writing style — PR can change how it adds cmcc,pz-l8
without affecting this patch.

Signed-off-by: CrazyBoyFeng <crazyboyfeng@gmail.com>

--- a/target/linux/qualcommax/ipq50xx/base-files/etc/hotplug.d/firmware/11-ath11k-caldata
+++ b/target/linux/qualcommax/ipq50xx/base-files/etc/hotplug.d/firmware/11-ath11k-caldata
@@ -51,6 +51,13 @@ case "$FIRMWARE" in
 		caldata_extract "0:art" 0x1000 0x20000
 		;;
 	yuncore,ax830|\
+	cmcc,pz-l8)
+		caldata_extract "0:art" 0x1000 0x20000
+		label_mac=$(mtd_get_mac_binary 0:art 0)
+		ath11k_patch_mac $(macaddr_add $label_mac 2) 0
+		ath11k_remove_regdomain
+		ath11k_set_macflag
+		;;
 	yuncore,ax850)
 		caldata_extract "0:ART" 0x1000 0x20000
 		label_mac=$(mtd_get_mac_binary 0:ART 0)
@@ -98,6 +105,13 @@ case "$FIRMWARE" in
 		ath11k_remove_regdomain
 		ath11k_set_macflag
 		;;
+	cmcc,pz-l8)
+		caldata_extract "0:art" 0x26800 0x20000
+		label_mac=$(mtd_get_mac_binary 0:art 0)
+		ath11k_patch_mac $(macaddr_add $label_mac 3) 0
+		ath11k_remove_regdomain
+		ath11k_set_macflag
+		;;
 	yuncore,ax830)
 		caldata_extract "0:ART" 0x4c000 0x20000
 		label_mac=$(mtd_get_mac_binary 0:ART 0)
